---
The Catacombs of Nightfall are classified as a Midgaard civic substructure under Ossuary Transport Court jurisdiction.
The Compact's shared apparatus — one registry, one warrant system — connected Nightfall to both the Gloamvault and the Dungeon Intake Yard through the same chain-of-custody architecture.
Municipal records categorize the complex under civic remainder processing: the administrative category created when lineage claim, religious rite, and burial charter all failed to attach to a body.
Ledgerhouse archives preserve intake manifests showing forest oath artifacts catalogued as civic remainder in the same intake queues as condemned prisoner effects.
Midgaard's current administrative position treats the catacombs as a heritage site with unresolved liability: pre-Compact oaths were voided by civic processing, but descendants continue filing lineage claims citing those oaths.
The Reckoning Faction has sought access to the deep registers for three generations without success. The complex is militarily secured by the Watch but administratively categorized as contested jurisdiction.
Access petitions must be filed through the Magistrate Ledgerhouse under contested heritage protocol, requiring three-witness verification of prior custodial claim.
The Containment Office treats any attempt to remove archive materials from Nightfall as a registry theft violation under Compact continuity law.

